Tana and Beles Sub basin organizations are sufficiently equipped with knowledge base and analytical tools for integrated water resources planning and management

baseline.value: No Sub-basin organizations at the beginning of the project

target.value: Interactive knowledge base products launched; knowledge base and analytical tools support sub-basin plan development for Tana andBeles subbasins.

actual.value: Tana Sub-basin Organization (TaSBO) and Beles Sub-Basin Organization (BeSBO) created and fully staffed. Analytical tools beingdeveloped and tested in each organization.

title.narrative: Flood Management Information System developed and used routinely

baseline.value: No existing effective system for flood forecasting and communication at regional-level

target.value: Flood forecasting and early warning system in place and used for the flood-prone areas around Lake Tana.

actual.value: Radar delivered and installation underway. Estimated completion date May 2015

title.narrative: Soil Erosion Monitoring and Evaluation system developed and monitoring network in place

baseline.value: No soil and water monitoring system is in place in the project area of Amhara region

target.value: M&E system and network for soil erosion monitoring and evaluation operational by Bureaus of Water Resource, Amhara region (formicro-watersheds) and TaSBO (for sub-watersheds)

actual.value: NRM baseline survey completed. M&E network established. Hydrological gauging stations at sub-watershed level established.Hydrological data has been regularly collected and analyzed.

title.narrative: Initial integrated basin management plans for Tana and Beles sub-basins developed and discussed by key stakeholders (regional bureaus and authorities, Basin Organizations, civil society organizations

baseline.value: No water resource plans for Tana and Beles sub-basins exist.

target.value: Sub-basin plans for Tana and Beles developed and discussed with key stakeholders.

actual.value: Draft water resources management plans for each sub-basin drafted and being reviewed through a series of stakeholder consultations.

title.narrative: Water resources monitoring network operational and information collected and used routinely

target.value: Enhanced HIS/BIS water resources monitoring network (including radar, gauging, and earth observation products) for Tana and Belessub-basins operational; Comprehensive Basin knowledge base and supporting analytical/ modeling tools used to support planning andoperational decisions.

actual.value: Equipment identified and ordered. Systems in place for installation and utilization once available. Equipments reached and sitessecured for installation.

title.narrative: Sub-basin organizations operational (With permanent heads appointed and core staff and approved basisn plans in place)

target.value: office buildings with adequate knowledge base, analytical tools, and capacity forsub-basin planning and management

actual.value: Sub-basin organizations staffed. Delays with physical infrastructure due to contractor performance - lack of inputs (anticipatedcompletion date May 2015)
